The article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House, notifying Congress that the national emergency with respect to the Western Balkans will continue beyond its anniversary date. The national emergency was declared in 2001 and is related to extremist violence in the Republic of Macedonia and other parts of the Western Balkans region, as well as acts obstructing the implementation of the Dayton Accords in Bosnia and United Nations Security Council Resolution 1244 relating to Kosovo. The letter states that these actions continue to pose a threat to national security and foreign policy interests of the United States.